From: Trung Le <trung.le@ruby-journal.com>
Subject: finish FHS migration for dtinfo and the data-only directories

Patch 0008 did most of the CDE_DATA_TOP split work but missed:

1. InfoLibSearchPath::InfoLibSearchPath has its own copy of the
   sysAdmConfig / factoryInstall reassignment. The factoryInstall side
   still uses CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP -- with --prefix=/usr that makes
   dtsearchpath probe /usr/infolib instead of
   /usr/share/cde/infolib, DTINFOLIBSEARCHPATH ends up empty, and
   dtinfo errors out with "No Infolib found or specified" /
   "Infolib specification format error".

2. backdrops/palettes Makefiles still install under
   $(CDE_DATA_TOP)/share/{backdrops,palettes} (the /share/ infix is
   a holdover from the legacy /usr/dt/share layout); the desktop's
   compiled-in DT_BACKDROPSEARCHPATH already looks at
   $(CDE_DATA_TOP)/{backdrops,palettes}.

3. programs/backdrops/Makefile.am has an install-data-hook that under
   FHS $(RM)s its own install dir and tries to create
   /usr/backdrops -> share/backdrops (root pollution). Drop it.

After this:
  * /usr/share/cde/backdrops/*.{pm,bm}      (was .../share/backdrops)
  * /usr/share/cde/palettes/*.dp            (was .../share/palettes)
  * dtsearchpath returns
      DTINFOLIBSEARCHPATH=/usr/share/cde/infolib/%L/%I.dti:...
  * dtinfo finds the bundled CDE User's Guide bookcase

--- a/programs/dtsearchpath/dtsp/InfoLibSearchPath.C
+++ b/programs/dtsearchpath/dtsp/InfoLibSearchPath.C
@@ -71,7 +71,7 @@ InfoLibSearchPath::InfoLibSearchPath

     // Need to re-initialize the defaults.
     user->sysAdmConfig   = CDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP;
-    user->factoryInstall = CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP;
+    user->factoryInstall = CDE_DATA_TOP;

     if (user->DTINFOLIBSP()) {
 	if (user->DTUSERINFOLIBSP()) {
--- a/programs/backdrops/Makefile.am
+++ b/programs/backdrops/Makefile.am
@@ -1,4 +1,4 @@
